Generic rejection email.

Thank you for your application to the graduate program at the California Institute of Technology. After carefully reviewing your application, the faculty has decided that they are unable to grant you admission. As you know, Caltech is a small school and as such we are able to admit only a small percentage of the applicants who apply each year. In many cases we are unable to offer admission to highly qualified candidates because of limited space and facilities, or because interests don't perfectly fit with the needs and research focus of our faculty. 

Your record and qualifications are very good, and we have no doubt of your ability to earn an advanced degree and that you will have a successful career.  We wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors. 

Best Regards,

Caltech Graduate Studies
